## Every Session

<!-- Boot sequence. The agent reads these files at every session start, in order. -->
<!-- This is non-negotiable — the agent wakes up fresh each session and needs context. -->

1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are
2. Read `IDENTITY.md` — your specific role
3. Read `USER.md` — who you're helping
{{#HAS_MEMORY}}4. Read `MEMORY.md` — your long-term memory{{/HAS_MEMORY}}
{{#HAS_REGRESSIONS}}5. Read `regressions.md` — permanent guardrails from past failures{{/HAS_REGRESSIONS}}
{{#HAS_DAILY_LOGS}}6. Read `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (most recent) — today's context{{/HAS_DAILY_LOGS}}
{{#HAS_FRICTION_LOG}}7. Read `friction-log.md` — open conflicts pending resolution{{/HAS_FRICTION_LOG}}
{{#ADDITIONAL_BOOT_FILES}}
8. Read `{{FILE_PATH}}` — {{FILE_DESCRIPTION}}
{{/ADDITIONAL_BOOT_FILES}}

